
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `lessfile` baraye baz kardan va didan mohtavay-e yek file matni (text file) be soorat safeh be safeh (page by page) estefade mishavad. In dastoor be shoma ejazeh midehad ke file-haye bozorg ra rahattar bekhanid.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `lessfile`  --> 📄 Baz kardan file be soorate sade.
    🔹 `lessfile +G`  --> 🏢 Raftan be akharin khatt dar file.
    🔹 `lessfile +F`  --> 📡 Monitor kardan file baraye taghirat jadid (mesle `tail -f`).
    🔹 `lessfile -N`  --> 🔢 Namayesh shomareye khatt-ha.
    🔹 `lessfile -g`  --> 🔍 Tanha khatt-haye marboot ra highlight mikonad.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ lessfile myfile.txt

    🔹 Baz kardan file "myfile.txt" baraye khandan.

    $ lessfile +G logfile.log

    🔹 Baz kardan file "logfile.log" va raftan be akharin khatt.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ lessfile -N important_notes.txt

    🔹 Baz kardan file "important_notes.txt" ba namayesh shomareye khatt-ha, ke baraye peygiri va refrence dadan asan tar ast.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `lessfile` command is used to open and view the contents of a text file page by page. It allows you to read large files more easily.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `lessfile` --> 📄 Open the file in a basic mode.
    🔹 `lessfile +G` --> 🏢 Go to the last line in the file.
    🔹 `lessfile +F` --> 📡 Monitor the file for new changes (like `tail -f`).
    🔹 `lessfile -N` --> 🔢 Show line numbers.
    🔹 `lessfile -g` --> 🔍 Only highlights the relevant lines

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ lessfile myfile.txt

    🔹 Open the file "myfile.txt" for reading.

    $ lessfile +G logfile.log

    🔹 Open the file "logfile.log" and go to the last line.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ lessfile -N important_notes.txt

    🔹 Open the file "important_notes.txt" with line numbers displayed, making it easier to track and reference specific lines.
